The tiny Kingdom of Glavia, nestled in the shadow 
of the great mountains of the north between two 
mighty rivers, has been beset by an invasion of
demons. The demons have destroyed everything, and 
driven off the poor inhabitants. The King of Glavia, 
distraught with grief, has disappeared into hiding 
with amnesia. Return his memory and his throne to him.

This is a difficult quest, however, there are many 
items you may find on the way which will help you 
in more than just the quest. Therefore, it may be 
worth your while to start now.

Note: you *will* need a helping hand during at least 
one part of the quest. Additionally, look at everything 
in detail, and use your other senses as well. Treat 
the area as you would the real world: actions have 
effects that may range far from your immediate vicinity. 
Logic should tell you what *should* happen when you try 
something, and for the most part, it will.

This is a mid to high level quest.
